<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8203532>
    dc:description "FIGURE 44. The external morphology and polyps of Chrysogorgia delicata Nutting, 1908. A, B. The same specimen in situ (the arrow) and after collection. C, F. Non-terminal polyps under a light microscope and SEM, respectively. D, G. Terminal polyps under a light microscope and SEM, respectively. E. A part of branch under SEM. Scale bars: 5 cm (B); 1 mm (C, D, F, G); 500 μm (H)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8203532/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8203536>
    dc:description "FIGURE 45. Sclerites of Chrysogorgia delicata Nutting, 1908. A. Sclerites in tentacle rachis. B. Sclerites in polyp body wall. C. Some warty sclerites in the proximal pinnules. D. Sclerites in coenenchyme. E. Sclerites in pinnules. Scale bars: 300 μm (A–E; A, B, D, E in the same scale)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8203536/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

